<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Nutrient Subdomains and Nutrition Careers</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
            color: #333;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: 20px auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        }

        h1, h2 {
            color: #27ae60; /* Green for health */
        }

        .subdomain {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
            padding-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .subdomain h3 {
            margin-bottom: 5px;
            color: #2ecc71; /* Lighter green */
        }

        .subdomain p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .demand, .colleges, .scholarships {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            margin-left: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Nutrient Subdomains and Nutrition Careers</h1>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Macronutrients</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Includes carbohydrates, proteins, and fats. These are essential for energy production, growth, and overall body function.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Micronutrients</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Includes vitamins and minerals. Though needed in small amounts, they are crucial for various physiological processes and preventing deficiencies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Dietary Fiber</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Essential for digestive health, regulating blood sugar levels, and promoting satiety. It's found in fruits, vegetables, and whole grains.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Hydration</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Focuses on the importance of water and electrolytes for maintaining body fluid balance, temperature regulation, and nutrient transport.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Phytonutrients</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Plant-based compounds with antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, found in fruits, vegetables, and herbs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="demand">
            <h2>Demand for Hotel Nutritionists</h2>
            <p>The demand for nutritionists in the hospitality sector is growing due to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Increasing health consciousness among travelers.</li>
                <li>Demand for customized dietary options and allergen-free meals.</li>
                <li>Emphasis on wellness and healthy eating in hotel menus.</li>
                <li>The rise of wellness retreats and health-focused tourism.</li>
                <li>The need for nutritionists to develop and analyze menus, provide dietary advice to guests, and train staff.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="colleges">
            <h2>Colleges for Nutritionists in India</h2>
            <p>Some prominent institutions offering nutrition and dietetics courses include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS), New Delhi</li>
                <li>National Institute of Nutrition (NIN), Hyderabad</li>
                <li>Lady Irwin College, University of Delhi</li>
                <li>Mount Carmel College, Bangalore</li>
                <li>Manipal Academy of Higher Education (MAHE), Manipal</li>
                <li>Sri Ramachandra Institute of Higher Education and Research, Chennai</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="scholarships">
            <h2>Scholarships for Nutrition Courses</h2>
            <p>Scholarships and financial aid options may include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Merit-based scholarships from universities and colleges.</li>
                <li>Need-based scholarships for students with financial constraints.</li>
                <li>Government scholarships for higher education in science and health-related fields.</li>
                <li>Scholarships from private organizations and foundations.</li>
                <li>Specific scholarships offered by institutions for nutrition and dietetics students.</li>
                <li>Research grants for advanced studies and projects.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Always verify scholarship details with the respective institutions or government websites.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
